direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry ---

orchestrator: |md
  **/docs-orchestrator**

  - <ticket> (required)
  - --pr, --source-code-repo
  - --mkdocs, --draft
  - --create-merge-request
  - reads docs-workflow.yaml step list
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Requirements ---

requirements: |md
  **Requirements**

  - two-pass fanout
  - pass 1: discovery agent
  - pass 2: one agent per req
  - assembles requirements.md
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Code analysis (conditional) ---

code-analysis: |md
  **Code Analysis**

  - wraps learn-code subagent
  - module map, API surface
  - ONBOARDING.md + registry
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

scope-req-audit: |md
  **Scope-Req Audit**

  - classify each requirement
  - grounded / partial / absent
  - one subagent per req
  - guards vs hallucination
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

pr-analysis: |md
  **PR Analysis**

  - wraps understand-pull-request
  - subagent, isolated context
  - PR-ANALYSIS.md
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Planning (llm) ---

planning: |md
  **Planning**

  - docs-planner agent
  - synthesize inputs
  - plan.md (module list)
  - stop if 0 modules
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Writing (llm) ---

writing: |md
  **Writing**

  - docs-writer agent
  - adoc (default) or mkdocs
  - update-in-place / draft
  - docs + step manifest
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Technical review (llm) ---

technical-review: |md
  **Technical Review**

  - claim validation vs code
  - technical-reviewer agent
  - HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
  - drives fix loop
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Style review ---

style-review: |md
  **Style Review**

  - docs-reviewer agent
  - Vale lint
  - 18+ style-guide skills
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Security review ---

security-review: |md
  **Security Review**

  - deterministic PII scan
  - docs-review-security checklist
  - agent-based analysis
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Quality gate (llm, conditional) ---

quality-gate: |md
  **Quality Gate**

  - 2 Opus judges (parallel)
  - doc_quality + intent_alignment
  - extract AC gaps
  - pass / fail
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Merge request (conditional) ---

create-merge-request: |md
  **Create Merge Request**

  - confirmation gate
  - feature branch if on main
  - commit + push
  - open MR (GitLab) / PR (GitHub)
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Diagnostics (output) ---

pipeline-diagnostics: |md
  **Pipeline Diagnostics**

  - run diagnostics script
  - failures + bottlenecks
  - context-pressure report
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Flow ---

orchestrator -> requirements
requirements -> code-analysis: "requirements.md\nwhen has_source_repo" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
code-analysis -> scope-req-audit: "ONBOARDING.md\nwhen has_source_repo" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
scope-req-audit -> pr-analysis: "when has_pr" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
pr-analysis -> planning: "PR-ANALYSIS.md"
planning -> writing: "plan.md"
writing -> technical-review: "docs + manifest"
technical-review -> style-review: "confidence"
style-review -> security-review
security-review -> quality-gate: "when has_many_requirements" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
quality-gate -> create-merge-request: "when --create-merge-request" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
create-merge-request -> pipeline-diagnostics: "MR / PR URL"

# --- Back-edges (fix loops) ---

technical-review -> writing: "fix, ≤3×" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
quality-gate -> writing: "fix, ≤2×" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
}
